cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use skill-cost in a paper, engineering-metrics blog post, or cost-analysis dashboard, cite it as follows."
title: "cost: multi-harness token-usage cost reporter for AI agent sessions"
abstract: >-
  skill-cost reads the JSONL session logs written by AI agent harnesses
  (pi, Claude Code, OpenAI Codex, opencode) and reports accurate USD cost
  per session using the LiteLLM canonical model_prices_and_context_window
  catalog. Prices auto-refresh weekly at runtime and daily upstream via
  GitHub Actions. Ships as an agent skill (SKILL.md) with a stdlib-only
  Python script and zero configuration.
type: software
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/gaia-research/skill-cost"
url: "https://github.com/gaia-research/skill-cost#readme"
keywords:
  - cost
  - token-usage
  - pricing
  - llm-cost
  - agent-skill
  - claude-code
  - codex
  - opencode
  - pi-coding-agent
  - anthropic
  - openai
  - litellm
  - developer-tools
authors:
